https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/5.2.x/spring-framework-reference/web.html#websocket

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Working with Websocket
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- raw WebSocket interactions (one connection per endpoint)
- WebSocket emulation through SockJS (client fallback)
- publish-subscribe messaging through STOMP as a sub-protocol (message routing)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Handshake
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HTTP request with Upgrade command to
use open TCP connection

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
When to use
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
It is the combination of low latency, high frequency, and high volume that make
the best case for the use of WebSocket.



